## Live tail streaming

- **`useSocketStream`** (`src/shared/hooks/useSocketStream.ts`) — core WebSocket to `/api/v1/ws/live`: connection, dedup, lag, drop tracking. Status: idle → connecting → live → closed/error
- **`useLiveTailStream`** (`src/features/explorer-core/hooks/useLiveTailStream.ts`) — wrapper injecting `teamId`; accepts `subscribeEvent`, `itemEvent`, `params`, `maxItems`
- Protocol: `{op: "subscribe:logs", ...params}` → server streams `{event: "log", data: ...}` + heartbeat every 15s
- Used by: Logs domain (`useLogsHubData`)

## Global refresh / auto-refresh

- **Zustand:** `src/app/store/appStore.ts` — `triggerRefresh()` increments **`refreshKey`** (also bumps on time-range changes).
- **Persisted state:** `selectedTeamId`, `timeRange`, `autoRefreshInterval`, `theme`, `timezone`, `comparisonMode`, `viewPreferences`, `recentPages`, `recentTimeRanges`
- **Runtime state:** `refreshKey`
- **TanStack Query:** Many hooks include `refreshKey` in `queryKey` to force refetch when the time window is unchanged. Use **`placeholderData: keepPreviousData`** on queries so refetches do not flash empty/loading UI.
- **Backend-driven dashboard panels** (`useComponentDataFetcher`, `useDataSourceFetcher`): **do not** put `refreshKey` in `queryKey`. Use stable keys and **`useInvalidateQueriesOnAppRefresh`** to `invalidateQueries` when `refreshKey` changes. Treat **loading** as `isPending && data === undefined`.

